{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that's an exciting part of the story, thank you.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I learned many years later how this very confusing last few days came about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Count Folke Bernadotte, B-E-R-N-A-D-O-T-T-E, he-- he was the head of the Swedish Red Cross and a member of the Swedish royal family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He wrote the book It may not be in the libraries anymore, but possibly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He went to plead with Himmler during the last terrible days of the war, in Germany, for the release of the Scandinavian prisoners out of Ravensbruck concentration camp, of which there were a few hundred.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Danish, Norwegian prisoners particularly, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I'm not sure about Finnish, but could be.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In any event, Himmler wouldn't hear of it and told him, let them all die.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- but Himmler remained in-- I'm sorry, but Bernadotte remained in Berlin and about a week later, Himmler could really see which way the war was going, and he decided to save himself.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he sent an emissary to get Bernadotte and he met-- the-- the two met in the wee hours of the morning in some dilapidated cafe.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Very interestingly, he describes how haggard and exhausted and dirty Himmler looked.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Himmler wanted Bernadotte to be the go-between on a peace between England and Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But Bernadotte turned him down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He said, no, this will have to be an overall peace treaty, not a piecemeal.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Bernadotte took this opportunity to tell Himmler that, do yourself some good, Himmler, because when the Allies come, they're going to string you up.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Release those prisoners.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] whereupon Himmler said, take them all out of Ravensbruck, not only the Scandinavian prisoners that he went for.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
